	<!-- Understanding -->
	<h2 id="understanding">Understanding the error messages from HeyseForms</h2>
	<p>This section provides information about some common error messages from HeyseForms.</p>  

	<h3>noauth</h3> 
	<p>If this error is shown, it means the user did not have the authorization to access that page. Please contact the <a href="mailto:ITS-Internship-Planning@umich.edu">ITS Internship Planning</a> Team for authorization.</p>  

	<h3>404 Error</h3> 
	<p>If this error is shown, it means that the page that the user was looking for can't be located. Please check ensure that the web address is correctly entered. You can also go back to the <a href="/home">home page</a>.</p>  

	<h3>405 Error (Method Not Allowed)</h3> 
	<p>If this error is shown, it means that the request method is known by the server but is not supported by the target resource. For example, an API may not allow calling DELETE to remove a resource.</p>  

	<h3>500 Error (Internal Server Error)</h3> 
	<p>If this error is shown, it means that the server encountered an internal error and was unable to complete the user's request. For HeyseForms, it is usually due to No Authorization issue. Please ensure that the user has the required authorization to access the page by contacting the <a href="mailto:ITS-Internship-Planning@umich.edu">ITS Internship Planning</a> Team. If problem persists, please contact the <a href="mailto:alvaradx@umich.edu">James Alvarado</a>.</p>  

	<h3>503 Error (Service Unavailable)</h3> 
	<p>If this error is shown, it means that the server is not ready to handle the request. Common causes are a server that is down for maintenance or that is overloaded. Please check the ITS page to see if there are any scheduled maintenance or if services are down. If problem persists, please contact <a href="mailto:alvaradx@umich.edu">James Alvarado</a>.</p> 

	<h3>504 Error (Gateway Timeout)</h3> 
	<p>If this error is shown, it means that the server is acting as a gateway and cannot get a response in time. Please try again later.</p>  

	<h3>Other Errors</h3> 
	<p>If any other errors occurred, the user can search online to learn more about the error codes. Please contact <a href="mailto:alvaradx@umich.edu">James Alvarado</a> if problem persists.</p>  
